7 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
8 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-149.7 of Title 70, unless
9 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
10 A. There is hereby created in the State Department of Education
11 the School Access for Emergency Response Grant Program to provide
12 grants to schools for needed interoperable communication hardware,
13 software, equipment maintenance, and training to allow for seamless
14 communications between first responder communications systems, new
15 or existing school district communications systems, and new or
16 existing school-based systems.
17 B. Grant recipients may use the money received through the
18 grant program for the following purposes:
19 1. To deliver training programs to teach district safety teams
20 and security personnel as well as appropriate school-based safety
21 teams and other personnel basic procedures for effective
22 communications with first responders in an emergency. The training
23 shall be based upon Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA)
24 Manual IS-0100.C: An Introduction to the Incident Command System.
